and then they stay in some ashrams maybe.

112
00:09:29,640 --> 00:09:32,800
They come to pujas,

113
00:09:34,240 --> 00:09:38,160
they listen to music, they may dance,

114
00:09:38,440 --> 00:09:41,400
they laugh, they're collective,

115
00:09:41,600 --> 00:09:45,400
but still their Guru Principle is not awakened

116
00:09:45,600 --> 00:09:49,080
unless and until they have created

117
00:09:49,280 --> 00:09:53,800
many, many more Sahaja yogis, Sahaja yogis.

118
00:09:57,600 --> 00:10:01,360
So the vision of a guru should be,

119
00:10:01,560 --> 00:10:06,200
"How many Sahaja yogis I am going to create?

120
00:10:06,400 --> 00:10:10,240
How am I going to use this creativity

121
00:10:10,480 --> 00:10:14,240
to create more Sahaja yogis?"

122
00:10:15,240 --> 00:10:20,680
So the basis or the essence of the Swadisthana Chakra,

123
00:10:20,880 --> 00:10:23,760
though is aesthetics,

124
00:10:24,360 --> 00:10:28,240
the force and the energy of Swadisthana Chakra

125
00:10:28,440 --> 00:10:31,200
is attention.

126
00:10:32,280 --> 00:10:35,440
If you have a wobbly attention,

127
00:10:36,520 --> 00:10:40,520
if your attention is one minute here, one minute there;

128
00:10:40,720 --> 00:10:45,120
if you have an attention by which you just can criticize ot

129
00:10:45,320 --> 00:10:48,000
and cannot see your own faults;

